    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi> (<hi rend="print">Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi>)</placeName>
                    <date>Nov. 24<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1880</date>
                    <seg type="supplemental"><hi rend="italic">Private</hi></seg>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                    <p>I am sorry to have to inform you that I do not believe in the Bible as a divine revelation, &amp; therefore not in Jesus Christ as the son of God.<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>Yours faithfully | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">0.1 (<hi rend="italic">Railway … S.E.R.</hi>)] <hi rend="italic">parentheses added</hi> </note>
            </div>
            
            
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">In his letter of <ref target="./DCP-LETT-12845.xml">23 November 1880</ref>, <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_3262.xml">McDermott</ref> had asked whether CD believed in the New Testament.</note>
        </div>
    
